==English==

===Etymology===
French; from the name of the inventor, Alphonse Bertillon

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: / bɛrtijɔ'naʒ /

====Hyphenation====
ber&middot;til&middot;lon&middot;age

===Noun===
'''bertillonage'''

Originally, a system for the identification of criminals making use of [[anthropometric]] measurements &#151; including head size, arm span, scars, distinguishing features and the like &#151; invented by Alphonse [[Bertillon]] (1853-1914). The usage has been extended to encompass a means of identification for racing greyhounds. It is often shortened to simply the name of the inventor, Bertillon.